Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with model-checking resource logics, which is a topic closely related to logic. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as resource logics are often used in AI for reasoning about resource allocation and scheduling. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper discusses the computational complexity of model-checking resource logics. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as resource logics can be used to reason about program behavior and resource usage. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also relevant as resource logics can be used to analyze and optimize resource usage in software systems.
